]], United States\n|{{small|Defended the [[UFC Flyweight Championship]]. Performance of the Night. Dillashaw tested positive in pre and post-fight drug tests for [[erythropoietin]] (EPO). Vacated the title on December 19, 2019.}}\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|align=center|13\u20132\n|[[Demetrious Johnson]]\n|Decision (split)\n|[[UFC 227]] \n|{{dts|2018|August|4|format=mdy}}\n|align=center|5\n|align=center|5:00\n|[[Los Angeles, California]], United States\n|{{small|Won the [[UFC Flyweight Championship]]. Fight of the Night.}} \n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|align=center|12\u20132\n|[[Sergio Pettis]]\n|Decision (unanimous)\n|[[UFC 218]]\n|{{dts|2017|December|2|format=mdy}}\n|align=center|3\n|align=center|5:00\n|[[Detroit]], [[Michigan]], United States\n|\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|align=center|11\u20132\n|[[Wilson Reis]]\n|TKO (punches)\n|[[UFC 215]]\n|{{dts|2017|September|9|format=mdy}}\n|align=center|2\n|align=center|0:25\n|[[Edmonton, Alberta]], Canada\n|{{small|Performance of the Night.}}\n|-\n|{{no2}}Loss\n|align=center|10\u20132\n|[[Joseph Benavidez]]\n|Decision (split)\n|[[The Ultimate Fighter: Tournament of Champions#The Ultimate Fighter 24 Finale|The Ultimate Fighter: Tournament of Champions Finale]]\n|{{dts|2016|December|3|format=mdy}}\n|align=center|3\n|align=center|5:00\n|[[Las Vegas, Nevada]], United States\n|{{small|Cejudo was deducted one point in round 1 due to repeated low blows.}}\n|-\n|{{no2}}Loss\n|align=center|10\u20131\n|[[Demetrious Johnson]]\n|TKO (knees and punches)\n|[[UFC 197]]\n|{{dts|2016|April|23|format=mdy}}\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|2:49\n|[[Las Vegas, Nevada]], United States\n|{{small|For the [[UFC Flyweight Championship]].}}\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center | 10\u20130\n| [[Jussier Formiga]]\n| Decision (split)\n| [[UFC Fight Night 78|The Ultimate Fighter Latin America 2 Finale: Magny vs. Gastelum]]\n| {{dts|2015|November|21|format=mdy}}\n| align=center | 3\n| align=center | 5:00\n| [[Monterrey]], Mexico\n| {{small|[[UFC Flyweight Championship|UFC Flywei